## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Supabase Setup**: You will need to create a Supabase project at [supabase.com](https://supabase.com) and provide:
> - `SUPABASE_URL`
> - `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
> - `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` (for the backend)
>
> I will provide the SQL schema to run in the Supabase SQL Editor.

> [!NOTE]
> The backend uses **FastAPI** (modern, fast Python framework) — this is the best fit for Vercel's Python serverless runtime. Is this acceptable, or do you prefer Flask/Django?

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated (Browser Testing)
1. **Start the dev servers** — `npm run dev` (frontend) + `uvicorn main:app` (backend)
2. **Open browser** and verify:
   - Landing page loads with correct theme, fonts, layout
   - Register → Login flow works
   - Submit a complaint → appears on user dashboard
   - Track complaint by ID
   - Admin login → admin dashboard shows stats
   - Admin can update complaint status
   - All pages are responsive (test mobile viewport)

### Manual Verification (User)
- Deploy to Netlify (frontend) and Vercel (backend)
- Create a Supabase project and run the provided schema SQL
- Test the full flow end-to-end on your phone and laptop
